        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-07T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-07T03:00:00-05:00" n="1017" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1017">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5493/11–749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-07T16:00:00+08:00">November 7, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 7—4:38 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1932. ReDeptel 725, October 20. In view interim developments and particularly
                    settlement labor dispute Attaché offices and Bacon’s undertaking get mediation
                    of club employees dispute, of course assume Peiping would be authorized make
                    appropriate changes text letter Chou En-lai but propose answer on basis general
                    reasoning to be set forth early telegram eliminate references “flimsy [pre]text”
                    and “USA would not countenance negotiations under duress”.</p>
                <p>Please authorize.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
